node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine.

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

Barcelona from night to day via @world_walkerz. ✨ Set on the country's northeastern coast, Barcelona is the cosmopolitan capital of Spain’s Catalonia region and is known for its wealth of art and impressive architecture. 🇪🇸

If you're planning a visit, bookmark this and add these items to your bucket list! 📝

𝟭𝟬 𝗕𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗴𝘀 𝘁𝗼 𝗗𝗼 𝗶𝗻 𝗕𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗲𝗹𝗼𝗻𝗮
1. Tour La Sagrada Família.
2. Marvel at Casa Batlló.
3. Feast on a food tour at La Boqueria. 
4. Enjoy green space at Parc del Laberint d'Horta. 
5. Discover masterpieces at the Picasso Museum.
6. Stroll the famous street of La Rambla. 
7. Explore the Palau de la Música Catalana.
8. Hang out in the seaside locale of La Barceloneta.
9. Shop at Portal del Angel or Passeig de Gracia.

Having a great amount of fun in Dubai with @ladnevaksu, where you can go on an epic sandboarding adventure amidst the desert. 🇦🇪

Have you ever tried sandboarding? 🙌🏼

Walking on water with @jeremietronet. 🤩 With spectacular weather, crystal clear waters, and beautiful scenery, kitesurfing in the Caribbean is surely an experience of a lifetime. 🏝

This was shot in St. Vincent and the Grenadines, a southern Caribbean nation comprising a main island, St. Vincent, and a chain of smaller islands. Boasting private islands, posh resorts, and abundant coral reefs, it's a haven for boaters, divers, and discerning island lovers. 🇻🇨

Have you explored the Caribbean yet and do you dream of traveling here?

📽 @jeremietronet 
📍 JT Pro Center, St. Vincent and The Grenadines
🎶 Vance Joy - Riptide

Cruising through Tenerife with @travelinghawks is an ideal way to spend the day. 😎 Known as the largest of the Canary Islands, Tenerife is a destination that beholds a unique charm. 🇪🇸

With golden stretches of sand, vibrant nightlife, and idyllic villages, Tenerife is the perfect destination for a sunny beach holiday. The island's sub-tropical location means mild and sunny weather all year round, too. 🌴

If you're planning a trip here, spring and fall are considered to be the best times to visit. Have you ever been to any of the Canary Islands? ✨

📽 @travelinghawks 
📍 Tenerife, Spain
🎶 Vanessa Carlton - A Thousand Miles

node.text:
In the last two weeks, wildfires have caused damage to tens of thousands of hectares of forest in Turkey's provinces, killing eight people and forcing thousands to flee. These wildfires are described as the worst in decades and show the devastating reality of the climate crisis we face today. 🚨

Prayers are not enough. If you can, please donate to @wwf @world_wildlife and other credible organizations leading the climate fight. You can also donate to the Wildfire Relief Fund set up by the @turkishphilanthropyfunds and GoFundMe pages for the wildfires in Turkey. 🇹🇷

Every little bit of help counts. If you know of any organizations or fundraisers that need support, please comment down below and share this post to help spread the word. 📣

📸 Grateful to @mishka_bochkaryov and @n__a__z__i__m for sharing these with the community 🙏🏽
📍 Turkey

Adventures with dad via @world.from.my.eyes. 👴 “One of the best trips of my life was when I went to Antarctica with my father. My father was way more active than I was. He did everything including hiking on glaciers, camping while it was snowing, and finally being on the top deck when we were stuck on 60 ft waves passing through Drake Passage (the roughest seas in the world).” 💙

While it’s easy to get caught up in today’s fast-paced world, it’s important to spend quality time with loved ones—like embarking on that once-in-a-lifetime adventure in Antarctica.

Where’s your dream family getaway? 🗺

📽 @world.from.my.eyes
📍 Antarctica
🎶 James Horner - Hymn to the Sea

Have you ever gone whale watching before? 👀

Dreamy and extravagant Cappadocia mornings via @muratkoksalart, where you can witness the iconic scenery of hot air balloons ebbing and flowing above valleys and "fairy chimneys". 🎈✨

Hot air ballooning is one of the most popular activities in Cappadocia. Though it's available almost all year round, the best time to experience it is from April to November, when weather conditions are more favorable.

Out of all your travels, what's the most surreal destination you've been to? 😍

📽 @muratkoksalart 
📍 Cappadocia, Turkey
🎶 Busta Rhymes - Touch It

Imagine setting your eyes on @timulrich.pix's view of Blausee, where crystal-clear waters, multi-colored trees, and soft rays of light paint a picture of a surreal, magical forest. 😌

One of the best-known mountain lakes in Switzerland, Blausee is nestled in the midst of a vast 20-hectare nature park.
